# ============================================================================
# Domain Contextualization Ontology - BFO 2020 Compliant
# ============================================================================
#
# Purpose: Models how different life domains appropriately weight worldview
# relevance to prevent absurd applications while respecting worldview plurality.
#
# Philosophical Foundation:
# This ontology addresses the critical insight that not all worldviews are
# equally appropriate in all contexts. Domain-specific contextualization
# prevents:
# 1. Absurd applications (e.g., spiritualism dominating surgery technique)
# 2. Hidden elimination of worldviews (domain weighting â‰  universal rejection)
# 3. Context-blind moral reasoning (different domains have different purposes)
# 4. False universalism (pretending all contexts are equivalent)
#
# Key Philosophical Sources:
# - Gould, S. J. (1997). Non-Overlapping Magisteria (NOMA): Science and religion
#   address different domains with different methods and purposes.
# - Walzer, M. (1983). Spheres of Justice: Different goods distributed by
#   different principles in different spheres (health, education, love, etc.)
# - MacIntyre, A. (1981). After Virtue: Social practices have internal goods
#   that determine appropriate virtues and standards.
# - Habermas, J. (1984). Theory of Communicative Action: Different action types
#   (instrumental, strategic, communicative) appropriate in different domains.
#
# Empirical Foundation:
# - Hedlund-de Witt, A. (2012). Exploring worldviews and their relationships
#   to sustainable lifestyles: Domain-appropriate worldviews predict behavior.
# - Tetlock, P. E. (2003). Thinking the unthinkable: Sacred values and taboo
#   cognitions. Domain violations trigger moral outrage.
# - Fiske, A. P., & Tetlock, P. E. (1997). Taboo trade-offs: Reactions to
#   transactions that transgress spheres of justice.
# - Rest, J. R. (1986). Moral Development: Moral reasoning shows domain-specific
#   variation (personal vs. conventional vs. universal domains).
#
# ============================================================================
